# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Marka .dockerignore — C# / .NET
# Covers: ASP.NET Core, Azure Functions, console apps
#
# Strategy: exclude everything that Docker doesn't need to build
# the image. The Dockerfile COPY steps should be explicit anyway.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Source control
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Editor / IDE metadata
.vs/
.vscode/
.idea/
*.code-workspace
.history/
**/*.user
**/*.suo

# OS junk
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbbs.db

# Build outputs — will be produced inside the image
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/artifacts/
**/publish/
**/bld/
**/[Ll]ogs/

# Test projects and results — not needed for production image
**/*Tests*/
**/*Test*/
**/*.Tests/
**/*.Test/
**/TestResults/
**/*.trx
**/*.coverage
**/*.coveragexml

# NuGet packages (restored inside Docker)
**/packages/
**/*.nupkg
**/*.snupkg

# Node.js / frontend (if separate build stage, adjust as needed)
**/node_modules/
**/.next/
**/dist/
**/build/

# Local secrets and config overrides
**/*.env
**/.env
**/local.settings.json
**/appsettings.*.local.json
**/appsettings.local.json

# Certificates / keys
**/*.pfx
**/*.p12
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/*.cer
**/*.crt
**/*.snk

# Docker files themselves (not needed inside image)
Dockerfile*
docker-compose*.yml
**/.dockerignore

# IaC / CI/CD (not part of the application)
infrastructure/
.github/
.azuredevops/

# Documentation and assets
**/*.md
**/*.txt
LICENSE
Assets/
docs/

# Misc scripts
**/*.ps1
**/*.cmd
**/*.sh
